    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-06-09</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-06-24T16:41:58Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Prohibits a railroad carrier from operating or causing to be operated a remote control locomotive to carry hazardous materials.</p> <p>Directs the Secretary of Transportation to issue a rule requiring that: (1) railroad carriers inventory and maintain continuous accounting of remote control transmitters, such transmitters be kept in a secure location when not in use, and be assigned only to personnel with proper identification and authorization to use them; and (2) the manual operational control area of any remote control locomotive be kept under lock and key when such locomotive is operated without personnel of the railroad carrier present.</p> <p>Sets forth civil penalties for a railroad carrier that violates such requirements, including criminal penalties if such violation involves the release of a hazardous material that results in death or bodily injury.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To prohibit the use of remote control locomotives to carry hazardous materials, and for other purposes.</title>
